Found this place about 2 months ago and really liked it. I've been coming in once a week while I'm in the area. Yesterdays experience was lacking to say the best. I ordered cheese garlic bread. That consisted of 1/2 oz vodka 1/2 oz triple sec , and 1/2 oz bar sour. Shaken and strained. The bartender pored this into a 1oz shot glass.....mixed shots are poured into rocks glasses. Basic math says 1 &1/2 ounces of liquid isn't going to fit Into a 1oz shot glass. Not to mention the dilution of shaking warm liquor in cold ice. Bartender common knowledge.  Anyway. She filled the shot glass I drank it and pushed the glass forward for her to finishing pouring the rest of the liquor I was paying for into my glass. She did. She then returned and told me 11$. In shock i said 11 for 1 shot . She said no, you had 2 shots. You must be kidding! Nope I was charged 11$ for 1oz of liquor plus mixer. Needless to say as much as I have enjoyed the food and atmosphere I will be changing my weekly stop and be giving another establishment my business.
